		 <bestPractices>
			<dos>
				<practice status="current" originDate="2010-05-31">This is a required field if affiliation information is being added.</practice> 
				<practice status="current" originDate="2010-05-31">This field can only be repeated by adding a new affiliation tag set.</practice> 
				<practice status="current" originDate="2010-05-31">Most often used to indicate publishers or meeting sponsors.</practice> 
				<practice status="current" originDate="2010-05-31" link1="events" style1="bold">All events must complete meeting sponsor information.</practice> 
				<practice status="current" originDate="2010-05-31" link1="books/monographs" style1="bold">All books/monographs, encyclopedias, encyclopedia entries, book chapters, book forewords, book reviews, refereed proceedings, newsletters and formally published interactive resources must complete publisher information.</practice> 
				<practice status="current" originDate="2010-05-31">May also be used to indicate authors, editors or contributors if the institution is playing that role.</practice> 
				<practice status="current" originDate="2010-05-31">Use the controlled vocabulary or enter a new institutional name.</practice> 
				<practice status="current" originDate="2010-05-31">Before using a new name, be sure to check the controlled vocabulary list carefully before entering the new institutional name.</practice> 
				<practice status="current" originDate="2010-05-31">Spell out new names completely, capitalizing all proper names and all major words.</practice> 
				<practice status="current" originDate="2010-05-31">If an external institutional name is provided already, double check for accuracy.</practice> 				
			 </dos>
			<examples>
				<practice status="current" originDate="2010-05-31" link1="UCAR" style1="bold">UCAR: University Corporation for Atmospheric Research (UCAR)</practice>
				<practice status="current" originDate="2010-05-31">Scripps Institution of Oceanography</practice>
				<practice status="current" originDate="2010-05-31">U.S. Bureau of Reclamation</practice>
				<practice status="current" originDate="2010-05-31">Universit&#0224; di Milano</practice>
				<practice status="current" originDate="2010-05-31">The World Bank</practice>
				<practice status="current" originDate="2010-05-31">National Institute for Environmental Studies (Japan)</practice>
			</examples>
			<otherPractices>
				<otherPractice header="Special Characters to Encode? Do This:">
					<practice status="current" originDate="2011-06-10" link1="numeric entity encodings" url1="http://theorem.ca/~mvcorks/code/charsets/auto.html">All special characters like subscripts, superscripts, copyright and other symbols must be entity encoded numerically. See the numeric entity encodings.</practice>
				</otherPractice>
			</otherPractices>
		 </bestPractices>
		 <documentation>
